==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Logomachy
<hw>Lo*gom"a*chy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/;
<grk>lo`gos</grk> word + <?/ fight, battle, contest: cf. F.
<ets>logomachie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Contention in words
merely, or a contention about words; a war of words.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The discussion concerning the meaning of the word
⟦ldquo⟧justification⟦rdquo⟧ . . . has largely been a mere
<qex>logomachy</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>L. Abbott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A game of word making.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Logometric</ent>⟦br⟧
